    {{Ada/--| pre: a /&#61; 0 and a >&#61; -1}}
    {{Ada/keyword|if}} a {{Ada/operator|1=/=}} 0 {{Ada/keyword|and}} a {{Ada/operator|1=>=}} {{Ada/operator|1=-}}1 {{Ada/keyword|then}}

== WiKi markup and Ada comments ==

OK:

 {{Ada/--| hello?}}
 {{Ada/--| ! pre: wlt > 0}}

But:

 {{Ada/--| result >&#61; 0}},
versus
 {{Ada/--| result >= 0}}
and
 {{Ada/--| count &#61; old count + 1}}
versus
 {{Ada/--| count = old count + 1}}


(From [Computer_programming/Design_by_Contract])

Resolution: look at this WiKi's [[meta:help:templates|templates]] syntax,
named and numbered parameters, like in {{Ada/operator|not_equals|1=/=}}.
IOW RTFM. Thanks to [[User:ManuelGR|ManuelGR]] for pointing this out.

